  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Millennium Water Alliance (MWA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation and maintenance of water schemes (wells, birkas, boreholes), development of new water schemes, training, natural resource management.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Millennium Water Alliance (MWA), a group of US-based NGOs, is dedicated to assisting 500 million poor people through advocacy and direct support to gain access to clean drinking water, improved hygiene and sanitation by 2015. MWA members have joined forces to implement the Millennium Water Program (MWP) to improve water and sanitation in Ethiopia. The program will be implemented exclusively in rural communities partly because of the enormous need for basic water and sanitation facilities and partly because the majority of the population live in rural communities. In addition, the program will impact a significant number of other stakeholders, particularly local and regional government staff, who will be involved in the capacity building components of the MWP. CARE, on behalf of the MWA, will manage the secretariat as well as implement one of the four sub-projects under the MWP. The sub-project, The Farta Water Supply and Hygiene Education Project, will target people in the rural areas of Farta Woreda (i.e. District) in the South Gondar zone of Ethiopia. The final goal is to contribute to the sustainable improvement in the health of targeted population through four key project components: water supply construction and development; training in water management; hygiene and sanitation promotion; and support to latrine construction.</narrative>
  </description>
